Hesperides

O apples of the Hesperides,

Keep your golden apples.
Let the West wind blow,
where the warm rivers flow,
Where the blue sea drowns
In the deep dark cups.
Let them build me a tower
That I may touch the sun,
In the wandering warm wind.

— H.D.

- HD
